:600ced8500000423  a    owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0097400 ;
        rdfs:comment    " While\nWT Act1 was able to restore IL-17-induced IκBα phosphorylation and degradation, JNK\nand ERK phosphorylation in Act1\n−/\n−\n MEFs, the D-Ubox mutant showed much reduced\nactivity (Fig. 2C). Theses data demonstrate that the U-box domain of Act1 is indeed\nimportant for IL-17-mediated signalling, implicating the importance of U-box-mediated E3\nubiquitin ligase activity in IL-17-induced Act1-mediated signalling." , "Through the use of the Ubc13-Uev1A E2 complex, Act1 mediated the lysine-63-linked ubiquitination of tumor necrosis factor receptor-associated factor 6 (TRAF6), a component of IL-17-mediated signaling. " ;
        layout:x        "3666" ;
        layout:y        "1009" ;
        dc:contributor  "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3394-9805" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7476-6306" ;
        dc:date         "2021-08-06" ;
        pav:providedBy  "http://informatics.jax.org" .

